 #define SANDBOX_LINUX_SYSTEM_HEADERS_LINUX_SECCOMP_H_
 
+// after #undef and even when placed before all other includes) results in the
+// preprocessor seeing the name position as a numeric constant (from prior
+// system headers pulled by the including .cc or by stdint/build_config/ioctl
+// etc.), producing the fatal "expected identifier before numeric constant"
+// while compiling broker_process.o (and the SIGSYS handler in trap.cc).
+//
+// The shim's only purpose for this constant was to give the value 1 to the
+// SIGSYS trap handler logic.  We therefore hard-code the literal 1 at the
+// single use site (sandbox/linux/seccomp-bpf/trap.cc) and never emit a
+// included cleanly while still providing the original sentinel behaviour.
+
